NAME
     map_2points - Return the angular distance between two points
     on the Earth's surface.

SYNOPSIS
     call  map_2points  (_l_o_n_0,  _l_a_t_0,,  _l_o_n_1,  _l_a_t_1,  _r_e_t__r_a_d_i_a_n,
     _r_e_t__m_e_t_e_r, _r_e_t__m_i_l_e, _r_e_t__r_a_d_i_u_s, _d_i_s_t)

DESCRIPTION
     map_2points return the distance between two locations of the
     Earth's surface, either in angular distance (in radians), or
     in great circle distance (in meters).

     _l_o_n_0, _l_a_t_0
          are the longitude and latitude of  the  starting  point
          [input].

     _l_o_n_1, _l_a_t_1
          are the longitude and  latitude  of  the  ending  point
          [input].

     _r_e_t__r_a_d_i_a_n, _r_e_t__m_e_t_e_r, _r_e_t__m_i_l_e, _r_e_t__r_a_d_i_u_s
          specify the return unit [input].  At  present  not  all
          avalaible.

     _d_i_s_t is the distance between the starting and ending  points
          [output].

OPTIONS
     NONE.

EXAMPLES
      real*8 lon,lat,lon0,lat0,dist
      call map_2points(lon0,lat0,lon1,lat1,0,1,0,0d0,dist)

